OL,3,CAsda beats big-name tea brands to be
OL,4,Cnamed nation's 'best cuppa'
OL,6,FPG Tips Original, costing #3 for 80
OL,7,Fbags, followed on 71%, with 68%
OL,8,Fjudging the colour to be "just how a
OL,9,Fcup of tea should look" while a
OL,10,Fsimilar proportion were satisfied with
OL,11,Fthe strength of bitterness.
OL,13,FTetley Original at #2.50 for 80 bags
OL,14,Falso scored 71%, with tasters judging
OL,15,Fthe tea to look good while offering a
OL,16,F"pleasant mouthfeel" and an enticing
OL,17,Faroma, with 54% agreeing that it had
OL,18,Fstrength of flavour. However, 27% said
OL,19,Fit was too bitter for their taste.
